B-Do you think that you can use the carat weight of a diamond to predict its price? THE plot shows a positive correlation between carat and price,The model showed an increase in price depending on carat weight,but as we see above that clarity with carat would give more better prediction for the price .

#Apply a log10 transformation to both the price and carat and save these as new columns in the data set called price_log10 and carat_log10.
jems.new<-select(jems,carat,price) %>%
mutate(carat_log=log(carat)) %>%
mutate(price_log=log(price))
jems.new

#10

#Using lm() to recreate a model that describes the relatioship shown in the plot
jems_lm <- lm(price ~ carat, data = jems)
jems_lm
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = price ~ carat, data = jems)
## 
## Coefficients:
## (Intercept)        carat  
##       -2256         7756
datatable(anova(jems_lm))
